  <sections xmi:id="_FELkoMflEd6iHPiFo39D4A" name="Link system blocks to non-functional requirements" guid="_FELkoMflEd6iHPiFo39D4A">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review the traceability record to determine the non-functional system requirements associated with the subject use&#xD;
    case.&amp;nbsp; Associate each non-functional system requirement for the subject use case with the relevant system block(s)&#xD;
    by creating&amp;nbsp;SysML &amp;lt;&amp;lt;satisfy&amp;gt;&amp;gt; dependencies from the system block to the requirement.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In some case it may not be possible to allocate the non-functional requirement as-is (for example, a mass&#xD;
    constraint).&amp;nbsp; In these cases the system level requirement must first be decomposed to yield&amp;nbsp;derived&#xD;
    requirements that together satisfy the system level requirement.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_UgIVQMflEd6iHPiFo39D4A" name="Update traceability records" guid="_UgIVQMflEd6iHPiFo39D4A">
    <sectionDescription>Update the Traceability Record to capture the&amp;nbsp;traceability between system blocks and associated non-functional&#xD;
requirements.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>Once functionality and associated performance requirements are allocated to the sub-blocks of a chosen architecture,&#xD;
non-functional requirements, such as design constraints, need to be allocated to the appropriate level: system, subsystem,&#xD;
component.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
